MerchantsPlaceDirty

Attributes describing each Merchant Brand to get the Place.

Field Required Type Description

country

required string

The country field is not mandatory but strongly suggested in order to refine and be able to differentiate logos from one country to another. The API accepts ISO-3166-1-alpha2 country codes only.

dirty_name

required string

The dirty name is the unique merchant identifier which is provided on transactions by a payment provider.

merchant_id

required string

Textual identifier for Merchant

city

optional string

The merchant’s city.

custom_id

optional string

This optional field allows integrators to send a value of their choosing and receive it in the body of the response.

description

optional string

The description is provided to you by the payment provider and is the transaction description attached to any payment.

position

optional object

The geographic coordinates where the transaction occurred. Sending in a position will significantly increase the possibility of finding a Place ID.

state

optional string

The merchant’s state.

street

optional string

The merchant’s street, typically found in the raw transaction.

zipcode

optional string

The merchant’s zipcode.
